---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | TSA Monster"
  description="TSA Monster's Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information, including our use of cookies, analytics, and affiliate links."
>
  <main class="flex-1 max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-slate max-w-none">
      <h1 class="font-display">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink-muted">Last updated: March 2025</p>

      <p class="lead">
        This Privacy Policy explains how TSA Monster ("we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, and
        protects information when you visit <strong>tsa.monster</strong>. By using this site, you
        agree to the practices described below.
      </p>

      <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>
        TSA Monster is a static, read-only website. We do not operate user accounts, registration
        forms, or comment systems. We do not collect names, email addresses, or other personally
        identifying information directly through forms on this site.
      </p>
      <p>
        The following information may be collected automatically through third-party services we use:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Log data:</strong> When you visit the site, our hosting provider may collect
          standard server log information, including your IP address, browser type, referring URL,
          and pages viewed. This data is used for security monitoring and aggregate traffic
          analysis — not for individual identification.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Analytics:</strong> We may use third-party analytics tools (such as Google
          Analytics or a privacy-first alternative) to understand how visitors interact with the
          site in aggregate. Analytics data is anonymized where possible and is never sold.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        TSA Monster does not set first-party cookies beyond what is technically necessary for site
        operation. Third-party services (including Amazon, Google, and analytics providers) may set
        their own cookies on your device when you interact with embedded links or scripts. You can
        control cookie behavior in your browser settings.
      </p>

      <h2>Affiliate Links and Amazon Associates</h2>
      <p>
        TSA Monster participates in the Amazon Services LLC Associates Program. When you click an
        affiliate link and make a purchase on Amazon, Amazon may set cookies to track that
        referral. This is governed by Amazon's own privacy policy, which you can review at
        <a href="https://www.amazon.com/privacy" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">amazon.com/privacy</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        We earn a small commission on qualifying purchases at no extra cost to you. We do not
        receive personally identifiable information from Amazon about your purchases — only aggregate
        commission summaries.
      </p>

      <h2>How We Use Information</h2>
      <p>We use collected information solely to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Understand how the site is used in aggregate, to improve content and structure</li>
        <li>Monitor for security issues and abuse</li>
        <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We do not sell, rent, or trade any information to third parties for marketing purposes.</p>

      <h2>Third-Party Links</h2>
      <p>
        Our reviews and articles contain links to Amazon and other third-party websites. Once you
        follow a link to an external site, that site's own privacy policy applies. We are not
        responsible for the privacy practices of third-party sites.
      </p>

      <h2>Your Rights</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on where you are located, you may have rights regarding your personal data,
        including the right to access, correct, or delete information held about you. Because we
        collect minimal data directly, most inquiries will relate to information held by our
        third-party service providers (Google Analytics, Amazon, our hosting provider).
      </p>
      <p>
        For any privacy-related questions or requests, contact us at{' '}
        <a href="mailto:hello@tsa.monster">hello@tsa.monster</a>. We will respond within 30 days.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy as our practices or applicable law changes. The "Last
        updated" date at the top of this page reflects the most recent revision. Continued use of
        the site after any update constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
